---
const localPrompt = `You are running in a local AI coding tool or terminal-based agent.

Goal: connect a simple workflow to my memory system.

The memory folder is the library. The workflow is the borrowing desk: before work, bring the right notes to the table. After work, put the new notes back.

First check:
- Can you create and edit files in this folder?
- Can you run shell commands if this tool supports them?
- Does a memory/ folder already exist?
- Is Superpowers installed or available in this tool?

If memory/ does not exist, create the basic memory structure first:
- memory/state.json
- memory/global/lessons/
- memory/projects/[project-name]/sessions/
- memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/
- memory/projects/[project-name]/workflows/

If Superpowers is not installed, help me install it:
- Claude Code: ask me to run /plugin install superpowers@claude-plugins-official
- Codex App: ask me to open Plugins in the sidebar, find Superpowers in Coding, click +, and follow the prompts
- Codex CLI: ask me to run /plugins, search for Superpowers, and choose Install Plugin
- Cursor: ask me to run /add-plugin superpowers in Agent chat, or search for Superpowers in the plugin marketplace
- If this tool does not support plugins, continue with the manual workflow rules below

If the tool needs me to click, approve, or restart, stop and tell me exactly what to do. Continue only after I confirm it is done.

Create or update these files:
- WORKFLOW_START_HERE.md
- memory/projects/[project-name]/workflows/basic-workflow.md
- memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/how-to-use-the-workflow.md

Also update the startup rules file for this tool:
- AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, .cursorrules, or the closest equivalent

WORKFLOW_START_HERE.md should include:
- Read MEMORY_START_HERE.md first if it exists
- Identify the current project
- Load memory/global/lessons/
- Load memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/
- Load memory/projects/[project-name]/workflows/basic-workflow.md
- Before meaningful work, choose one mode: brainstorm, implement, debug, review, or save
- Use Superpowers skills when available
- If Superpowers is not available, follow the manual workflow in basic-workflow.md
- Before saying work is done, check the result
- At the end of a meaningful session, write a session note
- Save reusable lessons in the right lessons folder

basic-workflow.md should use this shape:
- Title: Basic workflow
- Purpose: stop starting from a blank state
- Start: load memory and choose the work mode
- Work: follow the mode instead of guessing
- Check: verify the result before saying it is done
- Save: write the session note and reusable lessons
- Modes:
  - brainstorm: clarify the goal before making changes
  - implement: make the approved change
  - debug: find the cause before trying fixes
  - review: look for risks, bugs, and missing checks
  - save: capture what should carry forward

how-to-use-the-workflow.md should use this shape:
- Rule
- Why
- How to apply
- Boundaries

When setup is done, tell me:
- which files you created or changed
- whether Superpowers is installed, unavailable, or waiting for my action
- how the next session should start
- what I should ask for at the end of a session`;

const webPrompt = `You are in web/manual mode.

You cannot install plugins for me. You cannot save files for me. Do not say files were saved unless I confirm I saved them.

Goal: help me use a simple workflow with my memory system.

The memory folder is the library. The workflow is the borrowing desk: before work, bring the right notes to the table. After work, put the new notes back.

Ask me for the project name if you do not know it.

Generate the exact files I should save:
- WORKFLOW_START_HERE.md
- memory/projects/[project-name]/workflows/basic-workflow.md
- memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/how-to-use-the-workflow.md
- memory/projects/[project-name]/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-workflow-setup.md

For each file, use this format:

FILE: path/to/file.md
Then put the full file content in one markdown code block.

WORKFLOW_START_HERE.md must tell future chats:
- Read MEMORY_START_HERE.md first if I paste or attach it
- Ask me for memory/state.json
- Ask me for relevant files from memory/global/lessons/
- Ask me for relevant files from memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/
- Ask me for memory/projects/[project-name]/workflows/basic-workflow.md
- Before meaningful work, choose one mode: brainstorm, implement, debug, review, or save
- Follow the manual workflow because web chat cannot install local plugins
- Before saying work is done, ask how I want to check it
- At the end, output a session note for me to save
- If a reusable lesson appears, output the lesson file for me to save
- Do not claim anything was saved until I confirm it

basic-workflow.md should use this shape:
- Title: Basic workflow
- Purpose: stop starting from a blank state
- Start: load memory and choose the work mode
- Work: follow the mode instead of guessing
- Check: verify the result before saying it is done
- Save: write the session note and reusable lessons
- Modes:
  - brainstorm: clarify the goal before making changes
  - implement: make the approved change
  - debug: find the cause before trying fixes
  - review: look for risks, bugs, and missing checks
  - save: capture what should carry forward

how-to-use-the-workflow.md should use this shape:
- Rule
- Why
- How to apply
- Boundaries

The workflow setup session note should include:
- frontmatter with type, project, date, goal, outcome
- Goal
- What Changed
- Files To Save
- How To Start Next Time
- Lessons
- Follow-Up

After the file blocks, give me a short checklist:
- which files to save
- where to paste WORKFLOW_START_HERE.md if my web tool has project instructions
- what files to paste or attach at the start of the next chat
- what to ask for at the end of the next chat`;
---

<div class="prompt-tabs" data-prompt-tabs>
	<div class="prompt-tabs-header">
		<div>
			<p class="prompt-tabs-kicker">Choose one prompt</p>
			<p class="prompt-tabs-copy">Pick the workflow setup that matches how you use AI.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="prompt-tab-list" role="tablist" aria-label="Workflow setup prompt type">
			<button
				type="button"
				class="prompt-tab is-active"
				id="workflow-local-prompt-tab"
				role="tab"
				aria-selected="true"
				aria-controls="workflow-local-prompt-panel"
				data-prompt-tab="local"
			>
				Local tool
			</button>
			<button
				type="button"
				class="prompt-tab"
				id="workflow-web-prompt-tab"
				role="tab"
				aria-selected="false"
				aria-controls="workflow-web-prompt-panel"
				data-prompt-tab="web"
			>
				Web/manual
			</button>
		</div>
	</div>

	<section
		class="prompt-panel is-active"
		id="workflow-local-prompt-panel"
		role="tabpanel"
		aria-labelledby="workflow-local-prompt-tab"
		data-prompt-panel="local"
	>
		<div class="prompt-panel-bar">
			<p>Use this when the AI tool can edit files in your folder.</p>
			<button type="button" class="copy-prompt-button" data-copy-prompt>Copy local prompt</button>
		</div>
		<pre tabindex="0"><code>{localPrompt}</code></pre>
	</section>

	<section
		class="prompt-panel"
		id="workflow-web-prompt-panel"
		role="tabpanel"
		aria-labelledby="workflow-web-prompt-tab"
		data-prompt-panel="web"
		hidden
	>
		<div class="prompt-panel-bar">
			<p>Use this when you will save the files yourself.</p>
			<button type="button" class="copy-prompt-button" data-copy-prompt>Copy web prompt</button>
		</div>
		<pre tabindex="0"><code>{webPrompt}</code></pre>
	</section>
</div>

<script is:inline>
	(() => {
		const copyText = async (text, button, codeBlock) => {
			const originalLabel = button.textContent;

			try {
				await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
				button.textContent = "Copied";
			} catch {
				const range = document.createRange();
				range.selectNodeContents(codeBlock);
				const selection = window.getSelection();
				selection.removeAllRanges();
				selection.addRange(range);
				button.textContent = "Selected";
			}

			window.setTimeout(() => {
				button.textContent = originalLabel;
			}, 1800);
		};

		document.querySelectorAll("[data-prompt-tabs]").forEach((root) => {
			const tabs = Array.from(root.querySelectorAll("[data-prompt-tab]"));
			const panels = Array.from(root.querySelectorAll("[data-prompt-panel]"));

			tabs.forEach((tab) => {
				tab.addEventListener("click", () => {
					const target = tab.getAttribute("data-prompt-tab");

					tabs.forEach((item) => {
						const isActive = item === tab;
						item.classList.toggle("is-active", isActive);
						item.setAttribute("aria-selected", String(isActive));
					});

					panels.forEach((panel) => {
						const isActive = panel.getAttribute("data-prompt-panel") === target;
						panel.classList.toggle("is-active", isActive);
						panel.hidden = !isActive;
					});
				});
			});

			root.querySelectorAll("[data-copy-prompt]").forEach((button) => {
				button.addEventListener("click", () => {
					const panel = button.closest("[data-prompt-panel]");
					const codeBlock = panel.querySelector("code");
					copyText(codeBlock.textContent, button, codeBlock);
				});
			});
		});
	})();
</script>

<style>
	.prompt-tabs {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 1rem auto 0;
		border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #fff;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.prompt-tabs-header {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
		background: #f9fafb;
	}

	.prompt-tabs-kicker,
	.prompt-tabs-copy,
	.prompt-panel-bar p {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.prompt-tabs-kicker {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--black);
	}

	.prompt-tabs-copy {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--gray-dark);
	}

	.prompt-tab-list {
		display: inline-flex;
		gap: 0.25rem;
		padding: 0.25rem;
		border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #fff;
	}

	.prompt-tab,
	.copy-prompt-button {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		border: 1px solid transparent;
		border-radius: 6px;
		cursor: pointer;
	}

	.prompt-tab {
		padding: 0.45rem 0.7rem;
		background: transparent;
		color: var(--gray-dark);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.prompt-tab.is-active {
		background: var(--accent);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.prompt-panel-bar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1rem;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.prompt-panel-bar p {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--gray-dark);
	}

	.copy-prompt-button {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
		background: var(--black);
		color: #fff;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.copy-prompt-button:hover {
		background: var(--accent);
	}

	.prompt-panel pre {
		margin: 0;
		border-radius: 0;
		max-height: 32rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.prompt-tabs-header,
		.prompt-panel-bar {
			align-items: stretch;
			flex-direction: column;
		}

		.prompt-tab-list,
		.copy-prompt-button {
			width: 100%;
		}

		.prompt-tab {
			flex: 1 1 0;
		}
	}
</style>
